The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, July 04, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, July 4, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Festival				 																																	Odissi and Chhau dance from Mayurbhanj in the Orissa Festival at Swabhumi from 6 pm to 9.30 pm.				 																Fabrics				 																																	A collection of traditional textiles from Karnataka on display at Artisana, 13, Chowringhee Terrace, from 10 am to 7.30 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of rare contemporary Indian art at Gallery Caps, 16, Jatin Bagchi Road.				 																																	Paintings on view at Gandhara Art Gallery.				 																																	An exhibition of paintings and drawings by Arindam Chakraborty at Academy of Fine Arts from 3 pm to 8 pm.
